Common Languages Used on Tandem (NonStop)
1️⃣ TAL (Transaction Application Language)
Native Tandem language
Similar to C / Pascal
Used for low-level system and transaction processing
Very fast and efficient
2️⃣ TACL (Tandem Advanced Command Language)
Command-line scripting language
Used for job control, automation, file handling
Similar to Shell scripting
3️⃣ COBOL (NonStop COBOL)
Most widely used in banking & payment systems
Strong support for batch and online transactions
Still heavily used in legacy financial applications
4️⃣ C / C++
Used for performance-critical applications
System utilities and middleware development
5️⃣ Java (NonStop Java)
Used in modern integrations
Supports REST APIs and web services
Often used alongside legacy TAL/COBOL
